      "author": "LLLin000",
      "description": "## v1.4.17rc1 — Release Candidate\n\n**v1.6-v1.11 milestone consolidation.** Pre-release for user testing. Do not use in production yet.\n\n### What's in this release\n\n- **v1.6**: AI-ready literature asset foundation — canonical index, workspace migration, paper-meta.json\n- **v1.7**: Context-aware dashboard — lifecycle stepper, health matrix, maturity gauge, per-paper and collection views\n- **v1.8**: AI discussion recorder, deep-reading dashboard, Jump to Deep Reading\n- **v1.9**: Frontmatter rationalization, library-record deprecation\n- **v1.10**: Dependency cleanup — OCR/status/repair workers fixed to use formal note frontmatter\n- **v1.11**: Merge gate remediation — index path resolution, library-records cleanup, TUI removal, module hardening, repair blind spots, upgrade migration safeguards\n\n### Breaking changes from v1.4.16\n\n- **Directory names changed**: `99_System` → `System`, `03_Resources` → `Resources`, `05_Bases` → `Bases`\n- **Library-records removed**: All workflow state now lives in formal note frontmatter\n- **Setup is headless-only**: `paperforge setup` requires `--headless` flag; Textual TUI removed\n- **Python >= 3.10 required** (was 3.8)\n- **Upgrade migration**: Existing users should run `paperforge sync` once after upgrade to migrate legacy content\n\n### Known issues\n\n- First sync after upgrade may not reconcile legacy OCR/analyze flags from old library-records in all paths\n- Setup precheck does not validate Python version number (only checks Python is callable)\n- Interrupted upgrades can leave partially-migrated workspace directories\n\n### Files\n\n- `main.js` — Obsidian plugin\n- `manifest.json` — Plugin manifest\n- `styles.css` — Plugin styles\n- `versions.json` — Plugin version registry",
